The operation and the performance of the proposed solar driven adsorption cooling system were investigated by TRNSYS program (version 16). Through the TRNSYS studio, the proposed system is divided into components that are interconnected with each other. Each component is mathematically modeled by FORTRAN program. The TRNSYS model of the proposed solar adsorption cooling system for the present study in shown in Fig. 5. As shown in the figure, type 71 represents the evacuated tube solar collector where its mathematical model is described as follows [8]: the thermal efficiency of the solar collector and its outlet water temperature:Fig. 5
