The values of α0, α1, and α2 parameters are obtained from the manufacturer. Water storage tanks under condiseration are considered as thermally stratified tanks which are represented in TRNSYS by type 4. The stratified tank is modeled by dividing the tank into N horizontal sections. A set of N differential equations can be obtained due to energy balance for each section. The energy equation takes into account the energy gained and removed from both the supply and load circuits connected with the tank, in addition to the energy lost to the surrounding. The energy balance on a node i for a thermal storage tank can be expressed as follows [8]:3midTs,idτ=UsAscp,wTamb-Ts,i+FiCm˙CTC,o-Ts,i+Film˙lTl,r-Ts,i+qinter\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
